---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Words Ending in -ENCE — SEQUENCE, VIOLENCE, PRESENCE" description="Top -ENCE suffix Scrabble bingos: SEQUENCE (19pts), VIOLENCE (13pts), PRESENCE (12pts). Master the noun suffix for 8-letter bingo plays." keywords="scrabble ence words, sequence scrabble, violence scrabble, presence scrabble, ence suffix bingo, noun suffix scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words Ending in -ENCE — SEQUENCE, VIOLENCE, PRESENCE","description":"Master -ENCE suffix bingos in Scrabble: SEQUENCE (19pts), VIOLENCE (13pts), PRESENCE (12pts). Noun suffix bingos.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ence"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What are the highest-scoring -ENCE words in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SEQUENCE scores 19 points (Q=10), VIOLENCE scores 13 points (V=4, C=3), and PRESENCE scores 12 points (P=3, C=3). Q in SEQUENCE makes it the highest-scoring -ENCE bingo."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why is -ENCE a good suffix for bingos?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"-ENCE uses 4 tiles (E=1, N=1, C=3, E=1) costing 6 points. The C adds 3 points of value. With hundreds of valid -ENCE words and E being the most common tile, you'll find bingo opportunities frequently."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many valid -ENCE words exist in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Over 100 valid -ENCE words exist in SOWPODS. The suffix creates abstract nouns: DIFFER→DIFFERENCE, VIOL→VIOLENCE, PRES→PRESENCE, SEQU→SEQUENCE. Most are 8-10 letters, perfect for bingos."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words Ending in -ENCE — Noun Suffix Bingos</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">-ENCE transforms verbs and adjectives into abstract nouns — creating 8-letter bingos with elegant consistency. SEQUENCE brings Q into play for 19 points, VIOLENCE uses V for 13, and PRESENCE leverages P for 12. The C in -ENCE adds 3 points to every word, making this suffix score slightly above average for its length.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">19</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (SEQUENCE)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Suffix Tiles (ENCE)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid -ENCE Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Suffix Cost (E+N+C+E)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top -ENCE Bingo Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 SEQUENCE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">19 points · 8 letters · S(1)+E(1)+Q(10)+U(1)+ENCE(6) · Q = 10!</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 VIOLENCE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 points · 8 letters · V(4)+I(1)+O(1)+L(1)+ENCE(6)</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ PRESENCE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 points · 8 letters · P(3)+R(1)+E(1)+S(1)+ENCE(6)</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ EVIDENCE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 points · 8 letters · E(1)+V(4)+I(1)+D(2)+ENCE(6)</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">-ENCE Bingo Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Double E advantage:</span> -ENCE requires two E tiles — and E appears 12 times in the bag. When holding 2+ Es with N+C nearby, you're one root away from a bingo. Stop seeing double-E as weakness — it's -ENCE setup material.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SEQUENCE is the Q play:</span> Holding Q+U alongside E+N+C+E gives you SEQUENCE (19 + 50 = 69 points). This is one of the most reliable Q-bingos using mostly common tiles plus Q.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Pair with V for value:</span> VIOLENCE and EVIDENCE both use V productively. V is often hard to play well — -ENCE words give it a natural home inside a bingo worth 60+ points total.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SEQUENCE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">19pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VIOLENCE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PRESENCE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">12pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">EVIDENCE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">-ENCE needs <span class="text-white font-medium">two E tiles — and E is the most common letter</span> in Scrabble (12 copies). When holding 2+ Es alongside N+C, you're one root away from a bingo. Reframe double-E racks as -ENCE opportunities waiting to happen.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/words-ending-with-ence/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Words Ending With -ENCE</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ity/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -ITY</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-tion-guide/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -TION</span></a>
        
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-ending-in-ty/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Ending in -TY</span></a>
</div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find all -ENCE suffix words from your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
